result.formatted_address: 26 Java Rd, North Point, Hong Kong
result.name: Ipoh Mari

reviews.text: Tasty food with reasonable price. Support small restaurant and shops.
The curry laksa is tasty, close to what you get back in KL

Definitely overpriced for its food and I highly doubt the passion the owners have in food and hygiene. 

$68 for a 肉骨茶 which doesn’t come with a drink so I had to add a coffee which has an interesting name on the menu “檳城白咖啡” for $14, only to find out that it was instant coffee (supermarket has it at 15$ for 10 packs).... already speechless, the 肉骨茶 came and after halfway through eating, I saw an ant floating on the surface of the  soup.... 

Do not recommend this place at all and won’t be back.
Nice simple concept. Fairly decent Malaysian (Ipoh) style fast food. Choices are limited, but enough for a quick meal.

Owners were congenial. Food was decent. The portions were adequate. Would come back if I'm around the area. 
White coffee served in plastic cups.

result.adr_address: 香港北角渣華道26號
result.name: 姨婆瑪麗

reviews.text:
試過雞湯麵，醃雞的汁味道幾好，可是沒有附帶芽菜....五香豬肉卷新鮮炸起，幾香口。

下次有機會試下其他菜式。
Ｄ麵有好多菜送，正

姨婆瑪麗標榜正宗馬來西亞食品，在北角區較為稀有。由於店鋪面稹並不太大，故此在午餐及晚餐時段都頗多客人輪候，故選擇外賣的顧客亦不小。
最近選擇了蝦麫外賣，小辣、走炸葱，味道和在馬來西亞嘗試的蝦麫一樣美味，兩隻大蝦、魚蛋、雞蛋、通菜、炸腐竹、芽菜和油麫，分量不少。
伏！怎麼留言的人會説好吃？？？
음식은 깔끔하게 잘 나온것 같은데 내 입맛에 맞지는 않았다.
